<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
>

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-subscribers" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-bugs" />
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/form">
        <metal:heading fill-slot="heading">
          <div>
            <img alt="" src="/@@/question" />
            <a tal:attributes="href context/fmt:url" tal:content="context/title" />
          </div>
          <h1>Create a bug based on question</h1>
        </metal:heading>
        
        <div metal:fill-slot="extra_info">
            Please set the title to something relevant for a bug report.
            Review and change the bug description appropriately.
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<metal:help fill-slot="help">
  <p>If the problem described in this question is really caused by
    a bug in this project, you can create a new bug for it.
    You should make sure that the bug hasn't already be reported by searching
    for something similar first.
  </p>
  <p>Once the bug is created, a link will be recorded between that new bug and
    this question. You will able to navigate easily from one to the other.
  </p>
</metal:help>
</body>
</html>
